tip.text: Josh really took such great care of me. It's nice to feel heard and considered when dealing with something as personal as hair.
As tasty as you'd expect, but after the third bite of pure dough, it felt like enough.
Lemon bars, waffles, the egg sandwiches, coffee, chicken salad: pretty much everything here is most worthy of your mouth. Pricey, but that's the cost of consistent greatness. (And donuts on Saturday)
Down the short alley, past the plastic flaps, you'll find one of the best sushi meals of your life. Let the chef drive with the omakase, you'll be grateful you did.

venue.name: 十七代目 紀ノ重 築地本店

tip.text: How to begin??? The coolest arcade I've ever been to. Lots of vintage games. Darts and billiards and ping pong on the top floor. I'll be back and you should go.

venue.name: Kawasaki Warehouse (ウェアハウス 川崎店)

tip.text: Get the works. The duck is sublime, the dumplings are spiced perfectly, and the pork is tender and flavorful. The broth is strong, so bring your appetite.
Particular winners included the flounder, fatty tune, anything grilled with mayonnaise, and everything else I ate, too.

formattedAddress: 宇田川町21-1 (西武渋谷店 A館 8F)

venue.name: Katsu Midori (回し寿司 活 渋谷西武店)

tip.text: You'll be on the fast track to Diabetes Town, but you'll be smiling on the road there. That cronut is effing awesome. Filled with cherry and coconut cream.
Good ramen. I got the number 2, which wasn't as good as the number 1.

formattedAddress: 神宮前1-13-21 (シャンゼール原宿 2号館 1F)
location.crossStreet: シャンゼール原宿 2号館 1F

venue.name: Kyushu Jangara (九州じゃんがら 原宿1階店)

tip.text: That salted caramel donut had, to quote my friend, Bunny, "spectacular flavor." Also, the cat donut is the cutest thing I've put into my mouth today, so far.
Mind blowing. I've been to Kyoto a bunch of times now and this may have been the best meal I've had in the city. The okonomiyaki are works of art.

formattedAddress: 中京区梅忠町20-1 (三条通烏丸東入る)

tip.text: The lunch special is an incredible deal. If you're looking for a meal after a to a trip to an instant noodle museum, hypothetically, you'll be happy here.

venue.name: 権太呂すし 池田店

tip.text: Customizing your own Cup of Noodles is more fun than it has any right to be.

venue.name: The Momofuku Ando Instant Ramen Museum (インスタントラーメン発明記念館)

tip.text: Yes, you'll wait. You'll wait a while. Even at 3:00pm on a Wednesday you'll wait. But you'll be glad anyway. The Kyoto style has been my favorite, but you'll get what you want and feel like a winner.

formattedAddress: 新京極通四条上ル中之町580 (新京極通り四条上ル)
location.address: 新京極通四条上ル中之町580

venue.name: らーめん千の風 四条河原町店

tip.text: Loved this place. Broth is the star, with deep flavor. Excellent price, too.

formattedAddress: 中京区石屋町115 (木屋町通三条下ル 辻田ビル1F)
location.crossStreet: 木屋町通三条下ル 辻田ビル1F

venue.name: 博多長浜ラーメン みよし

tip.text: Broth is, somehow, simultaneously fatty tasting and watery. It's not a pleasant combination. Skip this is try for other places up here on the tenth.

formattedAddress: 下京区東塩小路町901 (京都拉麺小路)

venue.name: Araumado (あらうま堂 京都拉麺小路店)

tip.text: This the the pork Zeus would insist on, if Zeus ate ramen and wanted pork. It's something else, and melts, actually melts, in your mouth.

venue.name: Aoba-ramen Honmamon-ya (青葉らあめん ほんまもん屋)

tip.text: 1000¥ an hour feels like a lot. The cats are beautiful, and really used to people and each other. But, they are still cats, which means they are still lazy assholes.

venue.name: Ragdoll (猫カフェ ラグドール)

tip.text: Soy base broth is good, but not so good that you want to tip the bowl back and just drink it all like an animal. English menus were a surprise... A pleasant one!

venue.name: 元祖 岡山 とりそば太田

tip.text: Cute, laid back vibe that somehow feels special all the while reminding of tiny homespun burger joints all over the world. A strong highball doesn't hurt, either.
The karaage was pretty fucking great, too. Everything on every table looked killer.

Actually amazing, a complete surprise when we stopped in on instinct. Every looked amazing and Google Translate's photo option figures out the menu with remarkable aplomb. Sashimi bowl was to die for.
The yakiramen was enough to make the world slow down, and the grilled chicken wing wasn't any worse. That Mami is so nice and friendly only adds to the vibe.
Delicious. I don't know what's better, the soba or the machine translated reviews of the place. The omelette, by the way, is amazing.

venue.name: Shinshu Soba Murata (信州そばむらた)

tip.text: Cute. Popular with white people, like me. I tried the grilled pork burger (don't) and the big burger (really good, actually).
The best? No. But it is good, and the set menu is a nice sampling of what's regionally good to eat.
An antidote to a muggy evening: chocolate flavored ice, crushed Oreos, and condensed milk.
Calm, even when busy. Food is solid enough, staff is really friendly, the beach is clean, and your stuff will feel secure.

formattedAddress: Bãi Biển An Bàng (Hai Bà Trưng)

tip.text: The Vietnamese coffee with milk is a nectar the gods would drink, and the peach tea (without sugar) is perfection thanks to its lime leaf.
5 of the 6 beers I tried were revelations, with particular love to the floral passionfruit and an especially complex saison. Only the coffee porter felt like a miss (and I like porters...).
Bun cha is in the name, but the bo la lot is divine. Do yourself a favor and order one of everything, paying particular attention to the rice covered beef as well.
The coconut coffee is addictive and foolishly good. You'll feel like a fool, I say, a fool!
Pretty good, though I don't know it lived up to hype like "best in town." Still, how can I really judge? I'm just happy to be eating the Damn things.
Oh my. That was really so very good. And the ladies who work there are so nice to dumb foreigners who need help knowing what to do.
Easy wifi, chilled out vibe super cool and lots of seats. A great place to sit, read, and listen to boy bands.
Is it worth the wait? The wisdom of crowds doesn't miss on this one. Eat your sandwich and be glad the wait isn't longer.
My salad was mighty good. Pricey, as you'd expect a place with this level of professional polish to be, but it's nowhere near breaking your bank.
The Okinawa and the Hokkaido are both really good. Free wifi, and plenty of outlets. A rare bubble tea join that can be a study space.
Stick with the regular pho, if you're looking for soup. The eye is better than the brisket. Fried rolls are really good, too.
Great beers, cool menu, nice vibe that doesn't get too loud even when it's crazy crowded. And I've yet to be in a DC bar with prices this fair.
The mock meat is excellent. And I'm a meat eater. Got it with the citrus sauce and so effing good. And, believe me, I'm not one who appreciates much in the way of cuisine when out in Pikesville.
The pork is sweet, so be prepared for that, but so good. A great spot to grab and go, if you're ready for some Korean/Texmex hybrid.
Deep dish goodness. Delicious crust, and you can split the pie 50/50 to test the options. I loved the Kirkland.
Tasty, fast, satisfying, different. More CaliMex than straight Mexican, but that's not to put it down. Tried the pulled pork and the jerk chicken. Both good.
That cronut was decadent and delightful, but the glaze was on the thick side for me. If you liked baked sweets, this spot won't disappoint.
The tacos were delicious, I had the pastor, chorizo, and pescado. Each different, each good. Extensive menu filled with stuff I want to put into my mouth.
The proprietor is a super nice guy who will patiently answer all your questions if you are an obnoxious tourist with a lot of questions.
Cafe de Alma roasts their own coffee and are damn good at it. A really great place to sit, relax, and enjoy the spirit of Mostar.
I love pie, but I particularly loved this pie. Great beer selection. Wonderful coffee. But be careful, you may ask for three forks and get three slices of pie.
If the meat doesn't make you want to come back, Irma will. But the meat will make you want to come back, don't worry.
That baked apple is absolutely how you want to end your meal.
I certainly wasn't disappointed with the blueberry. And what traveler doesn't want a traditional Croatian cheese pie?
The chicken soup is so satisfying, and features two perfect parsley flavored matzo balls. The pork loin was magnificent, too, perfectly cooked.
The mixed pickles were a delicious starter. I would recommend the veal stew but make sure you are a bacon lover. The noodles are wrapped in a wall of bacon and while it is delicious, it is very rich.
Those knishes, so goddamn satisfying. And the soup felt so good on a cool autumn afternoon.
It's so filled with tourists and yet so complete itself. You have to go.
French Lady. Pumpkin soup. Toki pampas. All delicious. This place lives up to the hype.
Pastries look delightful. WiFi is done through 45 minute vouchers.
The meatballs are solid, portions large, though I wasn't quite as enamored with the place as I'd hoped.
I don't know what I ordered, but it was delicious and this place is goddamn cool.
I can't complain at all about that bacon sandwich. I didn't get it, but the Super Salad was huge and looked amazing.
Oh, that corn. You need to put it in your mouth.
They've got this pizza happy hour, it's late, but it's a great way to take advantage of the excellence of the place at reduced costs.
The cocktails are so fun and the ramen is sounding.
This was a satisfying experience. The via appia sandwich is worth a go.
The bowl is a tremendous deal. The flavors are strong, the portions are huge, and the veggies are satisfying. If you're looking for a fast and filling and delicious place for lunch, this is it.
The cold brew is smooth like butter. Plus the Ricks are so nice.
Let Janice make you a drink. I promise she won't disappoint.
Farmer's markets on Sunday!

formattedAddress: 玉門街1號 (圓山站花博園區)

tip.text: Amazing selection of bottles and cans from around the world alongside a modest selection of local craft on draft.

contact.facebookName: Crafted Beer & Co. 精釀啤酒屋

venue.name: Crafted Beer & Co. 精釀啤酒屋

tip.text: Great selection of draft beer. Cocktails looked very compelling. And the vibe of the place is so warm and inviting.
Menu! Now you know what they serve.
Loved the roasted pork - recommended by the dude who set up the menu. And thank goodness for green smoothie.
Even the decaf is good..
They say the buttermilk drop is best warmed up. Get them to warm it up.
Like others say, the crispy pork is excellent. So is the Tom yum.

location.state: จังหวัดกระบี่
formattedAddress: จังหวัดกระบี่

tip.text: Great selection of microbrew bottles, great vibe. A perfect place to grab a drink with a lady you're courting.

formattedAddress: 德行西路19號 (中山北路六段)

contact.facebookName: PIZZERIA OGGI拿坡里披薩專賣店

tip.text: That pizza oven is very serious business.

formattedAddress: 德行西路19號 (中山北路六段)

contact.facebookName: PIZZERIA OGGI拿坡里披薩專賣店

tip.text: Coffee is solid here and the WiFi is free.

formattedAddress: 中山北路七段36之1號1樓 (天母東路)

tip.text: So cussing cute. Coffee is tasty and the burritos are better than I could have hoped. What a neat place to stop.
Oh god, that breakfast polenta melted my face with its goodness.
Good atmosphere. The owner is a really nice guy. It's very small but has a very nice vibe. A local microbrews!
The curry is as excellent as people say, a fabulous mashup of Indian and Japanese influences, but curry with a selection of Japanese microbrews, as a jazz trumpet riffs in the background? Sign me up.
Expensive, but it makes every other eel I've ever eaten seem like a shadow.

venue.name: Asakusa Unatetsu (浅草うな鐵 国際通り店)

tip.text: There's predictably potato soup on Friday. Give it a shot.
That quiche was so good, and the berries were a perfect addition. What's a cute spot in an adorable and less trafficked area of town.
The absolute perfect place to spend an afternoon outside drinking. Nothing, nothing could be more perfect.
The secret men here are terrific. 10/10, must do.
Fried dumplings, mushroom casserole, and the surprisingly delicious cauliflower with shrimp paste. Eat it!

formattedAddress: 永康路132号 | 132 Yongkang Rd. (近襄阳南路 | at Xiangyang Rd. S.)
location.crossStreet: 近襄阳南路 | at Xiangyang Rd. S.

tip.text: Even to this carnivore, the vegan apple sage sausage is delicious. And thr guiness dog is great, too. Trust the staff on how to dress it up.
Dessert! So good. (the trout was excellent, too)
My cousin and I ate here and we enjoyed a lot of the tasting dishes. One of our waiters didn't really care to explain our dishes, but overall great food, and I liked the way the served the desert ;)
Everything. All of it. Especially the ant Hill dessert and the Tartar Azu
The BBQ chicken fries are AMAZING. And the burgers are are really good, too.
Good god, thats good juice. And the selection is big enough you could beat someone to death with. Shawarma is inedibly bad, though.
Fantastic latte. Very well balanced.

formattedAddress: Kemankeş Mah. Hoca Tahsin Sok. No:15A Karaköy
